The  Chicago Blackhawks  scored three
unanswered third-period goals to defeat the Detroit Red Wings
4-1 in the first game of their National Hockey League Western
Conference semifinal series.  In tonightâ€™s games, the  New York Rangers  open their Eastern
Conference best-of-seven series at the Boston Bruins and the
host Los Angeles Kings will try to extend their lead to 2-0 over
the San Jose Sharks.  Marian Hossa scored midway through the first period last
night for the Blackhawks and Johnny Oduya, Marcus Kruger and
 Patrick Sharp  added three goals in a little more than 11 minutes
of the final period at United Center in Chicago.  Damien Brunner scored the only goal for the Red Wings in
the first period. Detroit visits Chicago for Game 2 on May 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
